    <section class="section" id="prototype">
        <div class="content">
            <div class="grid-row">
                <div class="column-half">
                    <h3 class="heading">I prototype with code</h3>
                    <p>I sketch in code to create realistic, responsive, and interactive prototypes.</p>
                    <p>Using code enables me to focus on the technical considerations of a design: responsive flow, document hierarchy, performance, progressive enhancement, usability, and accessability. </p>
                    <p>By combining logic-less JS templating with dummy data I can quickly test an interface against edge cases and transient or empty states. </p>
                </div>
                <div class="column-half"><img src="images/svg/illustration/prototype.svg" class="illustration" /></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="test">
        <div class="content">
