                <div class="column-half--alt">
                    <h3 class="heading">I test with users</h3>
                    <p>Ideally, prototypes are tested with real users in real situations. However, I'm partial to guerrilla testing when deadlines are tight. Testing validates design decisions, evaluates usability, and uncovers subtleties not exposed during discovery. </p>
                    <p>Prototypes have a primary purpose; is my understanding and design thinking right or wrong?</p>
                </div>
                <div class="column-half--alt"><div class="placeholder"></div></div>
            </div>
        </div>
